---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Aetna International in Portugal', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-compliance', text: 'D7/D8 Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'portugal-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Portugal', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'us-expat-advantage', text: 'US Expat Advantage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'sns-transition', text: 'Transitioning to SNS', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Aetna', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Portugal', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs GeoBlue', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'portugalPrice', header: 'Portugal (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'visaCompliant', header: 'Visa Compliant' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Pioneer', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', portugalPrice: '$140-190/mo', visaCompliant: 'Check requirements' },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Prime', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', portugalPrice: '$190-260/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Platinum', coverage: 'Comprehensive', portugalPrice: '$260-350/mo', visaCompliant: true },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
  { key: 'portuguese', header: 'Portuguese Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)', aetna: '$190-260', portuguese: '€26-80' },
  { factor: 'US Coverage', aetna: 'Full integrated', portuguese: 'Not available' },
  { factor: 'Coverage Outside Portugal', aetna: 'Worldwide', portuguese: 'Limited' },
  { factor: 'Network in Portugal', aetna: 'Good (major cities)', portuguese: 'Extensive' },
  { factor: 'English Support', aetna: 'Full 24/7', portuguese: 'Limited' },
  { factor: 'Portability', aetna: 'Fully portable', portuguese: 'Must cancel' },
  { factor: 'Best For', aetna: 'US expats', portuguese: 'Long-term residents' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna International Health Insurance in Portugal"
  description="Guide to using Aetna International in Portugal. Ideal for US expats needing coverage in both countries. D7/D8 visa info, network, and pricing."
  headline="Aetna International Health Insurance in Portugal"
  subheadline="The best choice for American expats in Portugal who need seamless US healthcare access alongside their Portuguese coverage."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/portugal-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Aetna Portugal Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Aetna International in Portugal</h2>
  <p>
    Portugal has become a top destination for American expats—retirees drawn by the D7 visa, remote workers on the D8 Digital Nomad Visa, and families seeking European quality of life. For US citizens, Aetna International offers a compelling advantage: integrated coverage that works in both Portugal and the US.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're American and moving to Portugal, Aetna ensures you're covered when visiting family back home, seeing US specialists, or eventually repatriating—without paying the 40-60% premium increase other insurers charge for US coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">1.7M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers (incl. US)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">190+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Countries covered</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">24/7</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">English support</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Portugal-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Aetna International costs for US expats in Portugal."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-compliance">D7/D8 Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    Portugal's D7 (Passive Income) and D8 (Digital Nomad) visas require health insurance. Aetna International plans generally meet requirements, though as a US-based insurer, some consulates may request additional documentation.
  </p>

  <h3>Portuguese Visa Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Health insurance valid in Portugal</li>
    <li>Coverage for the visa duration (typically 1 year minimum)</li>
    <li>Comprehensive coverage including hospitalization</li>
    <li>Some consulates prefer EU-regulated insurers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Aetna Documentation</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Certificate of coverage</li>
    <li>Coverage confirmation letter</li>
    <li>Policy documentation showing benefits</li>
    <li>Translation assistance if needed</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Visa Tip</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Some Portuguese consulates (especially in the US) are familiar with Aetna and accept it readily. Others prefer EU-regulated insurers. If you encounter issues, consider <a href="/countries/portugal/insurance/allianz-care" class="underline">Allianz Care</a> for the visa, then switch to Aetna once approved. Or contact your specific consulate before applying.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="portugal-network">Network Coverage in Portugal</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna maintains a network of providers in Portugal, concentrated in Lisbon, Porto, and the Algarve—the areas with the most American expats.
  </p>

  <h3>Coverage by Region</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Lisbon:</strong> Multiple hospital options, strong specialist network</li>
    <li><strong>Porto:</strong> Good coverage at major private hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Algarve:</strong> Coverage in Faro, Lagos, and expat areas</li>
    <li><strong>Madeira:</strong> Funchal hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>Smaller cities:</strong> May need to travel or use reimbursement</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Key Hospitals</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Hospital da Luz (Lisbon, Porto)</strong> — Major private hospital group</li>
    <li><strong>CUF Hospitals</strong> — Extensive network across Portugal</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital Particular do Algarve</strong> — Key Algarve option</li>
    <li><strong>British Hospital Lisbon</strong> — English-speaking staff</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna offers Pioneer series plans. Pricing includes US coverage—making it more competitive than adding US coverage to other insurers.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices include worldwide coverage with full US access. USD pricing—consider exchange rate impact.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Navigator Plans (Modular Option)</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna's Navigator plans let you customize:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Core hospital coverage (required)</li>
    <li>Outpatient module</li>
    <li>Dental and vision modules</li>
    <li>Maternity module</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Navigator can reduce costs if you don't need all benefits—useful once you have SNS access for routine care.
  </p>

  <h2 id="us-expat-advantage">US Expat Advantage</h2>
  <p>
    The primary reason Americans in Portugal choose Aetna:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">US Coverage Benefits</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li>Full Aetna US network access</li>
        <li>Direct billing at US hospitals</li>
        <li>Aetna's negotiated US rates</li>
        <li>No separate US add-on cost</li>
        <li>Continuity if you repatriate</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why It Matters</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Visiting family in the US? Covered.</li>
        <li>US specialist needed? Direct access.</li>
        <li>Moving back? No coverage gap.</li>
        <li>No 40-60% US coverage premium.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="sns-transition">Transitioning to SNS</h2>
  <p>
    After establishing residency in Portugal, you can access the public healthcare system (SNS). Many expats keep Aetna even after SNS access:
  </p>

  <h3>Why Keep Aetna After SNS?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>US trips:</strong> SNS doesn't cover you in America</li>
    <li><strong>Private care:</strong> Faster access than public waitlists</li>
    <li><strong>English-speaking doctors:</strong> Easier to find privately</li>
    <li><strong>Travel:</strong> Worldwide coverage beyond Portugal/EU</li>
    <li><strong>Portability:</strong> If you move again, coverage continues</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Once you have SNS access, consider:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Higher deductible plan to reduce premiums</li>
    <li>Use SNS for routine Portuguese care</li>
    <li>Use Aetna for private care, specialists, and US trips</li>
    <li>Navigator (hospital-only module) if SNS handles outpatient needs</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Best for US Expats in Portugal"
    description="Integrated US coverage makes Aetna the smart choice for Americans."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Aetna</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Ideal For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>US citizens on D7 or D8 visas</li>
        <li>American retirees in Portugal</li>
        <li>Those who visit the US regularly</li>
        <li>People with US doctors/specialists</li>
        <li>Those who may repatriate</li>
        <li>US remote workers in Portugal</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Non-US expats (no US benefit)</li>
        <li>Those who never visit the US</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious (Multicare is cheaper)</li>
        <li>Those wanting EU-regulated insurer</li>
        <li>Settled permanently in Portugal</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is Aetna accepted for Portuguese D7 visa?</h3>
  <p>
    Generally yes, but it varies by consulate. Aetna is recognized international insurance. Some US-based consulates readily accept it; others may prefer EU-regulated options. Check with your specific consulate.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use Aetna while waiting for SNS registration?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Aetna covers you immediately. Use it for all healthcare until your SNS registration completes (which can take weeks or months).
  </p>

  <h3>Should I cancel Aetna once I have SNS?</h3>
  <p>
    Consider keeping it if you visit the US, want faster private care, or might relocate. If you're settled permanently and rarely travel, Portuguese insurance (Multicare, Allianz Portugal) may be more cost-effective.
  </p>

  <h3>Does Aetna cover Portuguese public hospitals?</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna is private insurance for private healthcare. Emergency care at public hospitals may be reimbursed. Routine SNS care is separate from your Aetna coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>How does Aetna compare to GeoBlue for Portugal?</h3>
  <p>
    Both are excellent for US expats. Aetna offers modular Navigator plans; GeoBlue offers the Blue Cross network. Similar pricing and coverage. <a href="/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue">See our comparison</a>.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Portugal?"
    description="Get a personalized Aetna quote for your Portugal move."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Visa requirements and network availability change. Verify all information with Aetna International and Portuguese authorities before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
